# Nuxt.js Guidelines

## Project Structure
- Follow Nuxt's convention-based project structure
- Use appropriate folder organization (pages, components, layouts, etc.)
- Leverage auto-imports for components and composables
- Use the ~/ alias for the srcDir
- Organize modules and plugins appropriately

## Page and Layout System
- Use the pages directory for routing
- Implement layouts in the layouts directory
- Use the composables directory for shared logic
- Leverage Nuxt's built-in components (ClientOnly, NuxtLink, etc.)
- Implement proper error handling with error.vue

## Composition API and Composables
- Use composables for shared logic
- Follow Vue 3 Composition API patterns
- Implement proper state management with useState
- Use lifecycle hooks appropriately (onMounted, etc.)
- Follow best practices for reactive data

## Server-Side Rendering (SSR)
- Implement proper async data fetching with useAsyncData
- Use server middleware for API routes
- Implement proper hydration handling
- Optimize for SEO with useHead
- Handle client/server differences appropriately

## TypeScript Integration
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Implement proper type definitions for composables
- Use Nuxt's built-in type safety features
- Leverage auto-generated types
- Implement proper type checking in templates

## Performance Optimization
- Use lazy loading for components when appropriate
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use prefetch and preload strategies
- Optimize images with @nuxt/image
- Leverage Nuxt's built-in optimization features

## Modules and Plugins
- Use official Nuxt modules when available
- Implement custom modules following Nuxt conventions
- Use plugins for extending Vue instance
- Follow module development best practices
- Leverage community modules appropriately

## Styling
- Use Nuxt's built-in CSS support
- Implement CSS frameworks with appropriate modules
- Use scoped styles or CSS modules
- Follow consistent styling patterns
- Implement responsive design principles

## Testing
- Use appropriate testing frameworks (Vitest, Cypress, etc.)
- Write unit tests for composables
- Implement end-to-end testing for pages
- Use Nuxt testing utilities
- Follow testing best practices

## Forms and Validation
- Implement form handling with appropriate libraries
- Use server-side validation when necessary
- Implement proper error handling and display
- Use client-side validation for UX
- Handle form submissions properly

## Security
- Implement proper input sanitization
- Use secure headers with nuxt-security
- Follow Nuxt security best practices
- Handle authentication securely
- Protect against common web vulnerabilities

## Build and Deployment
- Configure appropriate target (server/static)
- Optimize for different deployment platforms
- Implement proper environment handling
- Use Nuxt's built-in optimization features
- Follow deployment best practices

## Code Style
- Follow Vue and Nuxt style guides
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Maintain clean, readable code
- Use proper indentation and formatting
- Write clear, descriptive comments when needed